        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 16 at 4:13PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 413 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles east of Elbert, or 39 miles west of Limon, moving east at 20
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Simla and Fondis.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
